This article is a Presidential Memorandum from June 3, 2013, in which President Barack Obama delegates certain functions and authorities under the Iran Freedom and Counter-Proliferation Act of 2012. The memorandum delegates these functions and authorities to various government officials, including the Secretary of State, the Secretary of the Treasury, the Attorney General, the Secretary of Energy, the Secretary of Commerce, the Secretary of Homeland Security, the United States Trade Representative, the Director of National Intelligence, the Chairman of the Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System, the President of the Export-Import Bank, and other relevant agency heads. The memorandum outlines the specific sections of the Act that are being delegated and the responsibilities of each official. The Secretary of State is authorized and directed to publish the memorandum in the Federal Register.